We also note that while the majority of heterotrophic bacteria in our data set respire aerobically, there are a number of anaerobic strains, the majority of which were grown under various fermentation conditions. However, when we consider these groups of bacteria separately, we see no significant difference between their mean intra-specific thermal sensitivities (aerobic \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
