				\begin{document}$${t}_{d}=\mathrm{ln}(2)/\mu$$\end{document}td=ln(2)∕μ to calculate the maximum specific growth rate. Raw data were normalised to rates per second and degrees Celsius for use in modelling comparisons. In total, we collected 542 prokaryotic growth rate TPCs.

